Patch will not be uploaded to the list......get it at ::
http://www.dyer.vanderbilt.edu/
	server/udma/2.2.7.uniform-ide-6.19.delta.patch.gz
This is a major overhaul to mainstream various other platforms in to the
standard kernel IDE-Driver.  Every architecture is touched by these
changes.  If there is a problem with any part of this transistion patch I
need to know soon.  If the problems are to serve, then this will be
required to wait for 2.3.X.  If you have a need for any of the chipsets
listed below or generic features, your test is important.  Regardless if
you have/use/DGD (Don't Give a Darn) IDE devices, your test is important.
Anyone with soft-ide-raid, your test is important.
By now you should have the point.....
EVERYONE's TEST IS IMPORTANT.
If there is a breakage, fixit if you can or tell me what was error.
This is addressing changes to a critical sub-system of the OS.
FLAMES are not welcome, constructive suggestions are........
This includes new and updated chipset code and changes for ::
	ACER ali 1533/1543(C) IDE Driver
	Amiga Buddha and Catweasel IDE Driver
	CYPRESS CY82C693 chipset IDE controller
	Atari Falcon IDE Driver
	Amiga Gayle IDE Driver
	HighPoint HPT343(HPT345) IDE Driver
	Macintosh IDE Driver
	Promise Ultra/33 and Ultra/66 IDE Driver
		(Three cards full tuned, in testing)
	Promise DC4030 IDE Driver
		(Selectable idex, in testing)
	Intel PIIX IDE Driver
		(UDMA/DMA tuning, in the works)
	VIA MVP-3/TX Pro III IDE Driver
	CMD646 IDE Driver
	TRM290 IDE Driver
Andries B.
	Phoenix BIOS Geometry Code.
	EZ/DM translation geometry fixes.
Geert U. and Russell K.'s
	platform integration base model.
Russell King's
	dirty dma_cache clearing.
Mark Lord's
	patch: "DeviceFault" errors.
Gadi Oxman's
	ide-smart beginning integration.
Generic Ultra DMA 66 support.
Addition of IDE6 IDE7 for 16 devices and 8 interfaces.
The list goes on..........
PCI-BIOS quirks added in i386, may be need elsewhere for IDE-PCI cards.
